    205  6924							;===============================================================================
    206  6924							; ARM Direct Data
    207  6924							;----------------------------------------
    208  6924							;   I find it easier, and more space efficient, to store some of the data the
    209  6924							;   C code needs to access in the 6507 code instead of the C code.  Because the
    210  6924							;   build process is:
    211  6924							;
    212  6924							;	 1) assemble 6507 code to create defines_from_dasm_for_c.h
    213  6924							;	 2) compile C code to create ARM routines
    214  6924							;	 3) assemble 6507 to create final ROM
    215  6924							;
    216  6924							;   the ARM code could change size between steps 1 and 3, which would shift data
    217  6924							;   that immediately comes after it. So the data that C directly accesses needs
    218  6924							;   to be after an ORG to prevent it from moving.
    219  6924							;
    220  6924							;   The _IMAGE_GRAPHICS, _IMAGE_COLORS, etc data tables are directly access by
    221  6924							;   the C code so must be in the Direct Data area. The data they point to is
    222  6924							;   indirectly accessed by the C code, so they can go in the Indirect Data area.
    223  6924							;   Note the labels for the tables are prefixed by _ so they'll end up in the
    224  6924							;   defines_from_dasm_for_c.h file, while the labels for the data the tables
    225  6924							;   point to are not prefixed by _
    226  6924							;===============================================================================
    227  6924							;	  ORG $5F80
    228  6924							;	  ORG $5FFF
    229  6924							;_ARENA_INCREMENTS:
